title: For Sale:  Israeli UZI
postcontent:
For sale is an authentic I.M.I. ( Israel Military Industries) UZI, the civilian-legal, semi-automatic version of the classic sub-machine gun. These have been (and are still) used my military and police agencies around the globe, as well as numerous "special operations" types, including our own Secret Service. 
This rifle is the UZI B Model, imported by Action Arms, and is chambered in 9mm., and features a very sturdy collapsing stock, fully adjustable sights, both a traditional safety located on the receiver, as well as a grip safety (like a 1911) . It also has a ventilated barrel shroud that I put on it  (just 'cause they look so cool !!) 
 I've owned this rifle for about 10 years, having purchased it from the original owner, one of my oldest freinds, who originally purchased it around 1980.
The rifle is in excellent condition, has always fired flawlessly, and is surprisingly accurate.
 Included are 7 Israeli magazines ( one is a 25-rounder, the rest are 32 round mags), 4 of them are virtually brand new. Also included is the original canvas sling and mag pouch, as well as the original "dummy" barrel ( short presentation barrel, for looks only.) The heavy-duty,nylon case seen in the pic is included as well.
Asking $1400,firm, and this price is right in the middle of the range that these have been going for since well before any of the recent Assault-Weapons panics, so it's not an inflated price at all.
For what it's worth, I also have the original owners manual, but I can't find the damned thing !!! I would happily drop it in the mail if/when it ever pops up again.
Any prospective buyers must be Georgia residents, over 18, and able to prove it with valid Ga. drivers license. To sell to an Alabama resident, we'd have to do an FFL transfer (not difficult or expensive, but legally necessary.) 
I'm a legal Georgia resident with my Georgia concealed carry permit, so everything's good on my end.
Please respond via e-mail with any questions........thanks for looking.
